    "causal_summary": "Read-only bug + misalignment audit of the system-code-graph mk-code-index MCP server (~17.5k LOC). The operator dispatched the primary pass via cli-opencode using openai/gpt-5.5-fast at xhigh reasoning, which surfaced 3 contract findings (status read-only violation, unenforced tool schemas, trust-state enum drift). Claude verified each against source, added 3 database-path findings from the .opencode/.spec-kit directory-origin investigation, and ran a 43-agent completeness workflow that adversarially verified 32 of 36 additional candidates. The result is 37 confirmed findings (10 P1, 27 P2) recorded in review-report.md, including a WASM heap leak (tree-sitter Tree never deleted), a non-transactional removeFile, failed scans reporting fresh, and recovery operations that bypass the confirm gate. No source files were modified; remediation is deferred to scoped follow-on packets.",
